Parretti's departure, but it did not expect these activities to be reflected
in its results until next year.
For the first nine months, MGM suffered an operating loss of Dollars 79.4m
on revenues of Dollars 722.3m, compared with an operating loss of Dollars
110.9m on revenues of Dollars 703m a year earlier.
The company's net deficit for the 1992 period stood at Dollars 193.5m
against Dollars 233.2m.
Live Entertainment, the video distribution company 49.9 per cent owned by
the cash-strapped Carolco Hollywood studio, yesterday posted third-quarter
net income of Dollars 1.1m, or 5 cents a share, against a net loss of
Dollars 40.5m, or Dollars 3.39, last year.
Sales in the quarter rose to Dollars 91.2m from Dollars 85.7m.
The group said its improved results in the latest quarter were due partly to
higher sales and gross profit margins at Live Home Video.
In the 1991 third quarter, there was a Dollars 15m write-down in connection
with its acquisition of Vestron in July 1991.
The company said it expected its 'sales and profits will continue to reflect
this improvement in the fourth quarter'.
