<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 92 / Parliament and Politics: PPS posts are given to 'loyalists'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FIVE Conservative back-benchers from the 1992 intake yesterday became
parliamentary private secretaries - the unpaid 'eyes and ears' in the
Commons for ministers.
Downing Street described those promoted as 'loyalists' in an unspoken
reminder that Euro-sceptics and other rebels must mend their ways if they
seriously seek preferment.
The five were Mr Stephen Milligan (Eastleigh), Mr George Kynoch (Kincardine
and Deeside), Mr Hartley Booth (Finchley), Mr Jonathan Evans (Brecon) and Mr
Michael Bates (Langbaurgh).
