<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 92 / Vauxhall to cut output of cars
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
VAUXHALL, the UK subsidiary of General Motors of the US, is being forced to
cut its car output for the first time during the recession in the face of
weakening demand from export markets.
It is planning a cut of two shifts a week for four weeks in January at its
assembly plant at Luton, Bedfordshire, with a total production cut of 2,880
cars. Vauxhall's second plant at Ellesmere Port, Cheshire, will not be
affected by the cut.
Vauxhall's output this year is expected to reach a record of 300,000
vehicles.
