<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 92 / Ex-Bupa staff challenge court move
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN PIKE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A COMPANY formed by redundant staff of Bupa, Britain's largest private
healthcare group, will this week seek to overturn a court order secured by
their former employer, Alan Pike writes.
First Choice Health launched its Pure Health Plan - described as offering
'enhanced private medical cover for competitive premiums' - on November 2.
The following day, Bupa obtained a High Court order allowing it to search
the new company's offices.
A statement from First Choice Health yesterday said that its offices in
London, Beckenham and Bradford were raided simultaneously by Bupa on
November 4 'to search for evidence to substantiate suspicions by Bupa that
First Choice Health had been acting in breach of confidentiality in
obtaining business'.
It added that Bupa's suspicions were groundless, and that it was applying to
have the court order overturned. It would also seek costs and damages for
interference with its business.
Bupa confirmed that it had obtained the order 'to prevent misuse of Bupa
confidential information'.
</TEXT>
