FT  17 NOV 92 / International Company News: Paribas sees loss in cement deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PARIBAS, one of France's high prestige banks, will suffer a FFr600m (Dollars
115.3m) loss of profits this year because of its involvement with Ciments
Francais, the French cement company scarred by a scandal over its
off-balance sheet losses.
Ciments Francais, in which Paribas earlier this year agreed to sell a
controlling stake to Italcementi of Italy, has been clouded by controversy
since the discovery last month of off-balance sheet dealings of FFr1.05bn.
The company recently confirmed the dealings had cost it FFr655m in
exceptional losses during the first half of this year. This meant Paribas
faced a reduction in its capital gains on the sale of its shares to
Italcementi, and a fall in its share of Ciments Francais's estimated first
half profits.
Analysts anticipate net profits of less than FFr1.5bn from Paribas this
year, against a loss of FFr184m in 1991.
